              "link": "https://www.uline.com/Product/Detail/S-9936/Jars/Clear-Round-Wide-Mouth-Plastic-Jars-16-oz-White-Cap?pricode=WB0644&gadtype=pla&id=S-9936&ad_group_id=152179486982&gad_source=1&gad_campaignid=11612151543&gclid=Cj0KCQjwguLSBhDLARIsAH-yPrELFzXivNndELEB9E2T3k6Yjjk5g-u3pHuzmfw575vte0hAn15mJ2IaArQNEALw_wcB"
            },
            {
              "item": "Rigid mounting fixture",
              "quantity": 1,
              "specification": "Any fixture that fixes the jar along all 6 DoF in the perscribed starting configuration (e.g., tape).",
              "link": "https://www.mcmaster.com/76135A1/"
            },
            {
              "item": "Rigid Table",
              "quantity": 1,
              "specification": "Flat rigid work surface capable of holding manipulanda.",
              "link": "https://www.uline.com/Product/Detail/H-6979/Steel-Workbenches/Adjustable-Height-Machine-Table-24-x-18-x-18-25?pricode=WB6636&gadtype=pla&id=H-6979&ad_group_id=150516799157&gad_source=1&gad_campaignid=11612151768&gclid=EAIaIQobChMI2vHI1pKmlQMV_SbUAR01bglwEAQYASABEgLPJvD_BwE"
            }
          ],
          "setup": [
            "Secure the jar vertically to the table using the mounting fixture such that the jar cannot translate or rotate during the task.",
            "Place the lid flat on the tabletop with its open side facing downward and its center approximately 150 mm from the centerline of the jar.",
            "The manipulator shall begin each trial with the nearest point on the end effector at least 100 mm away from all of the manipulanda."
          ],
          "procedures": [
            "Position the manipulator in the prescribed starting configuration.",
            "Grasp and thread the lid until it is fully seated on the jar.",
            "A trial is considered successful if the lid is properly threaded onto the jar, fully seated, and remains attached to the jar after the manipulator releases contact."
          ],
          "metrics": [
            {
              "name": "Total Task Completion Time",
              "unit": "seconds",
              "description": "Time required to complete the task."
            }
          ],
          "executionConstraints": [
            "Any stategy can be used to accomplish the task.",
            "The manipulation system has 60 seconds to complete the task."
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "thread-screw-with-screwdriver",
          "title": "Use Screwdriver",
          "shortDescription": "Use a screwdriver to thread a screw.",
          "description": "Beginning with a partially threaded screw, grasp a screwdriver and use it to thread the screw an additional three turns.",
          "justification": "Use Screwdriver evaluates a system's ability to perform quasistatic indirect manipulation of a rigid object through the use of a tool. Relative to direct assembly tasks, screwdriver use introduces additional degrees of freedom associated with grasping, orienting, and stabilizing the tool while simultaneously controlling its interaction with the screw. The task exhibits high constraint complexity, as successful completion requires maintaining alignment between the screwdriver tip and screw head, generating sufficient torque to advance the screw, and regulating contact forces to prevent the driver head from camming out. It also involves substantial constraint change, progressing from free-space tool transport to tool engagement, threaded insertion, and final tightening. More broadly, screwdriver use serves as a representative benchmark for tool use and indirect manipulation, capabilities that are fundamental to many manufacturing, maintenance, and assembly operations.",
          "items": [
            {
              "item": "Phillips-head screwdriver",
              "quantity": 1,
              "specification": "Phillips-head #2 rubber grip screwdriver",
              "link": "https://www.mcmaster.com/5720A53/"
            },
            {
              "item": "Phillips-head screw",
