        {
          "id": "cut-pattern-with-scissors",
          "title": "Use Scissors",
          "shortDescription": "Pick up and use scissors to cut out a circle drawn on a piece of paper.",
          "description": "Pick up and use scissors to cut out a circle drawn on a piece of A4 printer paper.",
          "justification": "Use Scissors evaluates a system's ability to perform indirect quasistatic manipulation through an articulated tool while interacting with a deformable object. The task requires manipulating a pair of scissors whose dimensions are comparable to those of the hand while simultaneously controlling the motion and deformation of a sheet of paper. Relative to direct manipulation tasks, scissor use introduces additional degrees of freedom associated with the tool's articulation and coordination between the tool and the material being cut. More broadly, scissor use serves as a representative benchmark for articulated tool manipulation and tool-mediated interaction with deformable objects, capabilities that are important in manufacturing, medical, and household manipulation tasks.",
