          "justification": "Bundle Dowels with a Rubber Band evaluates a system's ability to coordinate manipulation of multiple objects while simultaneously handling a deformable fastening element. The task involves quasistatic direct manipulation of several rigid objects together with a deformable elastic object, requiring control over substantially more degrees of freedom than single-object manipulation tasks. Relative to simple relocation or assembly tasks, successful completion requires gathering, aligning, and maintaining a stable configuration of multiple independent dowels before manipulating the rubber band to secure the resulting bundle. The manipulator must manage contacts between the hand, multiple dowels, the table, and the rubber band while preserving the arrangement of the bundle throughout the fastening process. It also involves substantial constraint change, with contacts being repeatedly established and broken as dowels are collected, compressed into a close-packed configuration, and subsequently secured by stretching and wrapping the rubber band. More broadly, bundling objects with a flexible fastener is representative of many packaging, manufacturing, and household organization tasks that require coordinated manipulation of both rigid and deformable components.",
